posts.text: Not just some money. If you have super-voting shares, as so many founders do, you’re liable under the proposed tax as if you actually owned that much stock. So for Larry a 5% wealth tax becomes more like a 22% wealth tax.
posts.whyInteresting: Insightful commentary on how wealth taxes affect founders with super-voting shares.

posts.text: After we’d been in England for several years, I asked the people who do our taxes to check, and they told me that I actually saved money by moving to England. That’s how high California state taxes are already.
posts.whyInteresting: Personal anecdote comparing California and UK tax burdens for founders.

posts.text: if 70% of users skip your paywall, the price isn’t the issue — it’s the perceived value before the ask. Earn the payment emotionally before you request it financially.
